#DecolonizingEdVoicEd 
@agawap "Who we put in front of our children, matters."
#truth

“The data tells us a story – what meaning do we make of this data? Who narrates the issues? 

The communities who show up in our data are the people who we ask to narrate.“  Yes!

@mskikeojo #daring2do

“The real impactful doing is through the elimination of disparity and disproportionality – we will see it in the data! 
This is NOT rooted in ‘our’ feeling good, or a pat on the back – it’s the data!”
@mskikeojo #daring2do

Education Leaders - consider ..."What happens in your school board when you hear from racialized people?
 What do you 'do'with what you hear?"

@mskikeojo #daring2do

@Drawn2Intellect Thank you for this! Also....

Teach me about racism, but do NOT:
-  share narratives from 20 + years ago, because those stories from BIPOC aren't relative &amp; don't happen anymore

@DesmondCole "In understanding my own heritage, I was not taught about Black Loyalists or Freetown....
White supremacy is worldwide."

Reflecting on our responsibility as educators to share narratives besides the status quo that upholds this supremacy.

@Drawn2Intellect Performing Decolonization: Lessons Learned from Indigenous Youth, Teachers and Leaders' Engagement with Critical Indigenous Pedagogy 
Jeremy Garcia &amp; Valerie Shirley 
I learned...when schools privilege Indigenous knowledge, students are empowered to transform their communities.

With our Land - we can overcome! We can get our young people back. 
#truth #UnsettlingCanadaVoicEd 
